First Lady Michelle Obama gave a speech at the "Let's Move" South Lawn Kick-Off event, which aimed to promote healthy eating and exercise for children. She talked about the White House Kitchen Garden and how it sparked a conversation about eating right. The "Let's Move" campaign is a nationwide initiative to ensure that kids grow up healthy and learn skills to pass on to future generations. Mrs. Obama emphasized the importance of exercise and the lack of physical activity among children. She encouraged the kids in attendance to commit to getting at least 60 minutes of exercise every day and to inspire others to do the same. Trainers from local sports teams were present to teach the children various sports and activities. Mrs. Obama expressed her willingness to join in the activities and encouraged the kids to have fun while staying active. The speech concluded with a call to action for the children to make a commitment to their health and to encourage their families and schools to do the same.